description: Also known as Dongguandi Temple, or Dongmiao for short, it is a Guandi Temple in Seoul, located in Zhonglu District and outside Dongdaemun. It was built after the Wanli Korean War in 1599 and completed in 1601, funded by the Chinese government of the Ming Dynasty. There are also the South Temple, the North Temple, the West Temple, and the Middle Temple. The former was destroyed in the war and moved to the Tongque District. The latter three were later destroyed, and only the East Temple survived. It was designated as the 142nd National Treasure of Korea in 1963.

description: The first art museum in Seoul. Since its opening in 2009, the Seongbuk-gu Art Museum has established a sense of art identity through planned exhibitions centered on the history of Korean modern and contemporary art, and exhibitions that nurture key and emerging writers. At the same time, through the development and new establishment of various cultural and educational programs, it will become an art museum that can communicate with more people.
